# === Individuals: Features ===

effortless-ntwf:feat-keystone-actionability-gate a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-keystone-actionability-gate" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Four-gate clinical-actionability keystone" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Keystone / inference DAG" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "The entire system reduces to one computed boolean, `IndividualPredictions.IsClinicallyActionable`, TRUE only when all four derived gates hold (causally grounded, well-calibrated, non-spurious, ancestry-generalizable). Computed from a pure formula DAG, never entered. Seven synthetic patients land on both sides; each failure names the single deciding gate." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"col\": 223, \"len\": 87, \"quote\": \"individualized prevention, presymptomatic diagnosis, ancestry-equitable risk prediction\", \"section\": \"payoff\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1608, \"len\": 68, \"quote\": \"with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 351, \"len\": 79, \"quote\": \"identify the complete causal architecture of a heterogeneous autoimmune disease\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (payoff, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L6:223+87): _individualized prevention, presymptomatic diagnosis, ancestry-equitable risk prediction_
- **directly addresses** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1608+68): _with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:351+79): _identify the complete causal architecture of a heterogeneous autoimmune disease_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "This is the north-star reduction. It directly operationalizes the payoff paragraph's \"individualized... ancestry-equitable... actionable prediction\" and the prompt's demand for *calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations*. The four gates are the four hardest constraints in the prompt, each made a falsifiable boolean rather than a promise." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 3 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-trust-boundary-line-in-dag a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-trust-boundary-line-in-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Trust boundary as a line in the DAG" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Keystone / inference DAG" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Any field with a formula belongs to the model; any raw-input field is the human's (or the LLM's, as an overridable front-end). Every Z-stat, gate, and the keystone is a pure inspectable formula; nothing above the leaves is enterable. The trust boundary is literally an edge in the dependency graph." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1608, \"len\": 68, \"quote\": \"with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 66, \"col\": 191, \"len\": 37, \"quote\": \"decomposes into inspectable structure\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1608+68): _with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations_
- **indirectly supports** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L66:191+37): _decomposes into inspectable structure_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "This is the conceptual spine that makes the whole platform auditable rather than 'an LLM that diagnoses'. It is what lets the system claim *no reliance on spurious correlations* structurally (the V2 response: known reasoning *decomposes into inspectable structure*)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-llm-intake-clerk a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-llm-intake-clerk" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "LLM intake clerk" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Leaf / LLM surface" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "LLM reads a natural-language case and writes raw intake observation rows (ancestry, allele freqs, presenting facts) to base tables. It interprets the case like an intake nurse and never computes a single inference above the leaf layer." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 751, \"len\": 65, \"quote\": \"resolving cell-state-specific effects, allele-specific expression\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1446, \"len\": 83, \"quote\": \"accurately predict disease onset, severity, treatment response, and adverse effects\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:751+65): _resolving cell-state-specific effects, allele-specific expression_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1446+83): _accurately predict disease onset, severity, treatment response, and adverse effects_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Addresses the front of the challenge's data pipeline: turning heterogeneous clinical input into structured observations. The LLM is the *transcriber*, never the diagnostician - the half of the trust boundary that stays human-overridable." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-synthetic-lab a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-synthetic-lab" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Synthetic-but-transparent lab generator" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Leaf / LLM surface" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "LLM emits the case's test results (effect sizes/SEs, replication signs/p-values, permutation effect sizes, calibration coverage) as visible, sourced, editable leaf rows. The numbers are fake (the case is invented) but every value is transparent, sourced to the case, and editable." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 818, \"len\": 54, \"quote\": \"3D enhancer–promoter interactions, rare-variant burden\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1396, \"len\": 45, \"quote\": \"produce experimentally falsifiable mechanisms\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:818+54): _3D enhancer-promoter interactions, rare-variant burden_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1396+45): _produce experimentally falsifiable mechanisms_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Stands in for the prompt's enormous multi-omic measurement surface. The point isn't real biology (out of scope); it's that the *shape* real measurements would slot into exists, with each number a visible, correctable knob - defeating 'a hallucination laundered through a deterministic function'." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-three-panel-witness a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-three-panel-witness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Three-panel witness view" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Witness / harness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Input case text | extracted facts with per-fact provenance back into the text | deterministic diagnosis + four-gate trace. The middle panel is human-checkable independently of the verdict." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1608, \"len\": 68, \"quote\": \"with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1608+68): _with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "This is the anti-laundering instrument: it lets a reviewer verify the extracted leaves against the source text *before* trusting any derived conclusion. Indirectly serves the prompt's demand for *no reliance on spurious correlations* by making the raw->derived path inspectable end to end." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-witnessed-harness-home a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-witnessed-harness-home" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Witnessed red->green inference harness (home screen)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Witness / harness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "The app's home page IS a red/green test tree, not a form. Every category of inference (the DAG levels / the four gates) and the specific tests under each are asserted against the app's own API for all patients. As the model is built out, tests turn green; a fully green run is the proof." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1396, \"len\": 45, \"quote\": \"produce experimentally falsifiable mechanisms\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 66, \"col\": 191, \"len\": 37, \"quote\": \"decomposes into inspectable structure\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1396+45): _produce experimentally falsifiable mechanisms_
- **indirectly supports** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L66:191+37): _decomposes into inspectable structure_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The harness is how the platform makes its claims *checkable rather than asserted*. It is the operational form of the V2 response's argument: not 'how much is modeled' but 'does adding the next thing keep the audit guarantee' - and it stays green and inspectable when it does." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-knob-edit-ui a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-knob-edit-ui" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Knob-editing admin UI" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Witness / harness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Every LLM-produced leaf value is an editable field; correcting it re-derives the DAG. Every formula is inspectable/correctable in place, like a spreadsheet cell, so a wrong input is nudged, not re-prompted." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1608, \"len\": 68, \"quote\": \"with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1608+68): _with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Makes the trust boundary *actionable* for a human reviewer: the model's judgment is externalized into editable bottom-row cells, and all reasoning lives in the open DAG above them." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "loop-2" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-gate-explainability a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-gate-explainability" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Gate explainability" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Witness / harness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "For a patient, show why each gate passed/failed by walking one level down (coverage, cross-ancestry replication count, permutation survival, cryptic-relatedness flag, etc.)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1545, \"len\": 62, \"quote\": \"from ancestries and environments absent from the training data\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1608, \"len\": 68, \"quote\": \"with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1545+62): _from ancestries and environments absent from the training data_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1608+68): _with calibrated uncertainty and no reliance on spurious correlations_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Turns the keystone from a verdict into an explanation. Directly serves the prompt's *calibrated uncertainty* and ancestry-generalizability requirements by exposing the exact sub-evidence each gate rests on." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "loop-3" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-disease-state-machine a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-disease-state-machine" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Disease-state machine derived from raw labs" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Disease-state simulation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Disease progresses as a state machine: Presymptomatic -> SerologicActive -> EarlyNephritis -> RenalFlareRisk -> BiopsyIndicated. The current state is computed from rising anti-dsDNA + falling complement + proteinuria - never entered - and dwell time per state is tracked." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 34, \"col\": 569, \"len\": 69, \"quote\": \"the difference between an evidence gate and a disease-state simulator\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 51, \"col\": 0, \"len\": 63, \"quote\": \"Disease now progresses as a state machine derived from raw labs\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1019, \"len\": 56, \"quote\": \"feedback between disease progression and molecular state\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L34:569+69): _the difference between an evidence gate and a disease-state simulator_
- **directly addresses** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L51:0+63): _Disease now progresses as a state machine derived from raw labs_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1019+56): _feedback between disease progression and molecular state_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Directly answers the doctor's central v1 critique: the difference between an evidence gate and a disease-state simulator. This is the 'is the disease progressing' layer, built additively onto the same trust boundary (labs are the clinician's input; state is the model's derivation)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 3 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-sledai-activity-score a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-sledai-activity-score" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Derived SLEDAI disease-activity score" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Disease-state simulation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A SLEDAI activity score (and activity tier) computed per patient from the serology series (renal points, serology points, proteinuria), not a label anyone typed. Drives the worked nephritis example: rising anti-dsDNA, falling complement, renal-flare risk, biopsy-indicated." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 34, \"col\": 275, \"len\": 62, \"quote\": \"This patient is transitioning from presymptomatic autoimmunity\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 32, \"col\": 518, \"len\": 67, \"quote\": \"the clinical workflow from referral, differential diagnosis, workup\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L34:275+62): _This patient is transitioning from presymptomatic autoimmunity_
- **indirectly supports** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L32:518+67): _the clinical workflow from referral, differential diagnosis, workup_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Concretely supplies the 'real disease activity scores' the doctor named as missing in v1, and produces the first computed worked example: a patient *transitioning toward early lupus nephritis*." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-treatment-line-recommendation a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-treatment-line-recommendation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Derived treatment-line recommendation with one stated reason" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Treatment reasoning" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A recommended treatment line with a single stated reason, differentiated by the confirmed mechanism and the disease state: mycophenolate induction for active nephritis, anifrolumab for an IFN-pathway mechanism, belimumab for autoantibody-driven, secukinumab for IL-17/23." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"col\": 348, \"len\": 60, \"quote\": \"therapies that target each person’s causal molecular pathway\", \"section\": \"payoff\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 34, \"col\": 473, \"len\": 85, \"quote\": \"would likely respond differently to mycophenolate versus belimumab versus anifrolumab\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 55, \"col\": 37, \"len\": 67, \"quote\": \"A derived treatment-line recommendation with a single stated reason\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (payoff, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L6:348+60): _therapies that target each person's causal molecular pathway_
- **directly addresses** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L34:473+85): _would likely respond differently to mycophenolate versus belimumab versus anifrolumab_
- **directly addresses** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L55:37+67): _A derived treatment-line recommendation with a single stated reason_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The doctor's *second* worked example, computed. Implements 'therapies that target each person's causal molecular pathway' as a derived field grounded in a confirmed CausalMechanism node - a mechanism match, not a broad immunosuppression label." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 3 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-treatment-response-mechanism-match a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-treatment-response-mechanism-match" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Treatment-response prediction via mechanism match" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Treatment reasoning" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A treatment-response prediction is trustworthy only when the treatment targets a confirmed causal mechanism (IsMechanismMatched) AND the treatment is effective. A drug aimed at a debunked mechanism, or one that didn't work / was adverse, is never 'predicted to respond'." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1446, \"len\": 83, \"quote\": \"accurately predict disease onset, severity, treatment response, and adverse effects\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"col\": 633, \"len\": 29, \"quote\": \"reduce failed clinical trials\", \"section\": \"payoff\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1446+83): _accurately predict disease onset, severity, treatment response, and adverse effects_
- **indirectly supports** (payoff, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L6:633+29): _reduce failed clinical trials_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "One of the three prediction types the prompt asks for (onset / severity / treatment-response). Grounds treatment response in the same causal-mechanism DAG so it can never be a free-floating label." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-emergent-serology-cluster a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-emergent-serology-cluster" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Emergent serology-signature cluster (corpus-level discovery)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Corpus-level discovery" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A per-patient IsInPreNephriticSignatureCluster rolled up from each person's raw serology series (rising anti-dsDNA + falling complement), no label assigned. On the synthetic cohort it lands cleanly - 6 of 12 in the cluster - and perfectly separates active/progressing from quiescent patients." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 62, \"col\": 63, \"len\": 36, \"quote\": \"discovery is inherently corpus-level\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 62, \"col\": 340, \"len\": 66, \"quote\": \"surfaces as a derived emergent cluster across the whole population\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 351, \"len\": 79, \"quote\": \"identify the complete causal architecture of a heterogeneous autoimmune disease\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L62:63+36): _discovery is inherently corpus-level_
- **directly addresses** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L62:340+66): _surfaces as a derived emergent cluster across the whole population_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:351+79): _identify the complete causal architecture of a heterogeneous autoimmune disease_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Answers the doctor's deepest point: discovery is inherently corpus-level - a single chart never discovers a mechanism, a pattern across many patients does. This is the *shape* of discovery on synthetic data: membership emerges from the population's raw data and tracks the disease." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 3 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-evidence-disease-disagreement a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-evidence-disease-disagreement" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Evidence-gate <-> disease-state disagreement detector" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Corpus-level discovery" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Flags the patient where the disease-state simulator and the actionability gate disagree: the disease is clearly progressing (biopsy-indicated, high activity) yet the prediction is correctly judged not clinically actionable (a relatedness-leakage problem)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 57, \"col\": 95, \"len\": 63, \"quote\": \"the disease-state simulator and the actionability gate disagree\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 34, \"col\": 569, \"len\": 69, \"quote\": \"the difference between an evidence gate and a disease-state simulator\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L57:95+63): _the disease-state simulator and the actionability gate disagree_
- **directly addresses** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L34:569+69): _the difference between an evidence gate and a disease-state simulator_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The single clearest proof that disease-state simulation is a *second, independent* layer and not the old evidence gate relabeled. A system that only gated evidence could never say 'needs attention now, but our mechanism prediction isn't trustworthy enough to pick a targeted therapy.'" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-cohort-discovery-board a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-cohort-discovery-board" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Cohort discovery board (corpus surface)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Corpus-level discovery" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Top nav item for every role: the disease-state map, the emergent serology-signature scatter (with the derived cluster drawn as a halo, not a painted colour), the disagreement board, and the treatment-line distribution - all reading derived fields." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"col\": 312, \"len\": 30, \"quote\": \"precise patient stratification\", \"section\": \"payoff\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 62, \"col\": 63, \"len\": 36, \"quote\": \"discovery is inherently corpus-level\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **directly addresses** (payoff, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L6:312+30): _precise patient stratification_
- **indirectly supports** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L62:63+36): _discovery is inherently corpus-level_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The corpus-level surface where discovery is *expressed*. Moves the platform from per-patient adjudication (v1) to a population view, which is where the prompt's 'causal architecture' lives." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 2 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-diagnosis-writeup a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-diagnosis-writeup" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Per-patient diagnosis writeup" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Reporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Doctor-style Markdown writeup (-> diagnosis.pdf once green) produced as an artifact of a passing run: 'The patient presented with... tests xyz confirmed abc... therefore C (actionable / not, and the single deciding reason).' It needs no UI to be valuable." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"col\": 223, \"len\": 87, \"quote\": \"individualized prevention, presymptomatic diagnosis, ancestry-equitable risk prediction\", \"section\": \"payoff\", \"relation\": \"direct\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **directly addresses** (payoff, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L6:223+87): _individualized prevention, presymptomatic diagnosis, ancestry-equitable risk prediction_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The real output of the platform is a diagnosis, not a screen. This is the human-facing payoff that the prompt's 'presymptomatic diagnosis' and 'individualized' language ultimately asks for." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-derived-report-fragments a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-derived-report-fragments" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Derived narrative fragment fields" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Reporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Per-row calculated text fields that turn each fact into structured natural language, predicate-gated and case-by-case (e.g. TemperatureNarrative -> 'normal temperature' | 'light fever' | 'severe fever' from the row's own value). Each fragment is one spreadsheet-cell formula reading sibling fields and __meta__ phrases only - no joins or aggregations - composed upward into complex sentences." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 66, \"col\": 191, \"len\": 37, \"quote\": \"decomposes into inspectable structure\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **indirectly supports** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L66:191+37): _decomposes into inspectable structure_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Keeps all narrative wording inside the auditable DAG: the writeup is assembled from inspectable calculated cells, never free-text generated at render time. Reporting stays on the trust boundary." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-report-meta-phrasebook a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-report-meta-phrasebook" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Global phrasebook in __meta__" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Reporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Reusable, contextual language atoms stored once in the __meta__ settings table - literal global phrases ('The patient presented with...') and shared banding vocabulary - referenced by fragment fields so common language is authored/corrected in one place, never re-implemented per case." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "_No direct challenge clause - internal scaffolding._" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "DRY for narrative: the one place global phrasing is corrected. Supports the writeup feature without duplicating wording across patients." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 0 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-report-renderer a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-report-renderer" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Thin Python report renderer (replaces handlebars)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Reporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A small Python renderer whose only job is to read each patient's derived fragment fields from vw_* views and concatenate the non-empty, predicate-gated fragments in order into the diagnosis report (Markdown -> diagnosis.pdf). All sentence wording lives in the rulebook as calculated fields; the renderer owns no business or narrative logic." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "_No direct challenge clause - internal scaffolding._" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Enforces the rule that the renderer is dumb and the rulebook is the single source of narrative truth - the same discipline this PLATFORM_FEATURES.md generation itself follows." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 0 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-report-total-coverage-check a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-report-total-coverage-check" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Report total-coverage harness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Reporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "Tests that every patient word and every linked DAG node down to ground truth is represented in that patient's report (see tfs-report-covers-every-word, tfs-report-covers-every-dag-node)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "_No direct challenge clause - internal scaffolding._" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Closes the loop on the writeup: nothing in a patient's record is silently dropped from their report, and nothing in the report is unsourced. Total coverage is itself a witnessed test." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 0 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-explainer-dag a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-explainer-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "In-app Explainer DAG (clickable field provenance)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Platform infrastructure" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A generated, embedded visualization of the rulebook's calculated-field DAG: click any cell/field and see exactly how it was derived (raw inputs -> lookups -> calcs -> aggregations), with RuleSpeak prose baked in at transpile time." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 66, \"col\": 191, \"len\": 37, \"quote\": \"decomposes into inspectable structure\", \"section\": \"response\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **indirectly supports** (response, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L66:191+37): _decomposes into inspectable structure_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Makes 'the trust boundary is a line in the graph' literally clickable. Any reviewer can trace a verdict back to the raw leaves it rests on - the in-app form of the audit guarantee." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-url-driven-routing a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-url-driven-routing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "URL-driven routing & role navigation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Platform infrastructure" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "The URL is the single source of truth for view state: every thing/list has a stable URL, F5 restores the exact view+tab, and links reach any piece. Role trees (admin / intake clinician / ...) gate what each role can create/read/update/delete, derived from the RoutingAndNavigation rows." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 32, \"col\": 518, \"len\": 67, \"quote\": \"the clinical workflow from referral, differential diagnosis, workup\", \"section\": \"audit\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "- **indirectly supports** (audit, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L32:518+67): _the clinical workflow from referral, differential diagnosis, workup_" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Workflow scaffolding the doctor named as missing: referral -> workup -> monitoring needs addressable, role-scoped navigation. Permissions are derived from the rulebook, not hand-wired per screen." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 1 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-reverse-sync-db-to-rulebook a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-reverse-sync-db-to-rulebook" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Reverse-sync DB -> rulebook (input spoke)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Platform infrastructure" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "vw_* raw + computed values are written back into the rulebook data[] (snapshot-to-rulebook), so edits made in the running app round-trip into the hub. A 'Save to rulebook' admin action and the init-db snapshot step keep the hub and the DB mirrored." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered "_No direct challenge clause - internal scaffolding._" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "Makes the running app a peer input spoke to the rulebook hub, not a downstream dead end - the mechanism by which knob edits in the UI become durable rule-state." ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 0 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:feat-coverage-map-honesty a effortless-ntwf:Features ;
    effortless-ntwf:featureId "feat-coverage-map-honesty" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Honest coverage map (modeled vs. vocabulary-only)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "Platform infrastructure" ;
    effortless-ntwf:priority "Load-bearing" ;
    effortless-ntwf:description "A clause-by-clause map against the original challenge plus an honest scorecard: each capability is marked DEEPLY MODELED, SCHEMA-MODELED, or VOCABULARY / OUT-OF-SCOPE (IsDeeplyModeled / IsSchemaModeled on DiseaseDomainConcepts). What is derived says so; what is only named says so too." ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefs "[{\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1085, \"len\": 78, \"quote\": \"infer counterfactual disease trajectories without randomized perturbation data\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1325, \"len\": 37, \"quote\": \"privacy-preserving federated datasets\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}, {\"file\": \"THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"col\": 1254, \"len\": 69, \"quote\": \"batch effects, missing tissues, measurement error, ascertainment bias\", \"section\": \"prompt\", \"relation\": \"indirect\"}]" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeRefsRendered """- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1085+78): _infer counterfactual disease trajectories without randomized perturbation data_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1325+37): _privacy-preserving federated datasets_
- **indirectly supports** (prompt, `THE-ORIGINAL-CHALLENGE.md` L4:1254+69): _batch effects, missing tissues, measurement error, ascertainment bias_""" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengeNotes "The integrity feature. It directly confronts the prompt's own breadth - counterfactual trajectories, federated privacy, batch effects - by stating exactly which clauses are real derivations and which are vocabulary only. This is what keeps the platform 'a proof of shape, not a sales pitch.'" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refCount 3 ;
    effortless-ntwf:assignedLoop "" .

